data.text:
Robert Akpan aka Youngbobby age 17 born in West Orange, New Jersey has shown the signs of a prominent emerging artist from Atlanta. Originating from Akwa Ibom state in Nigeria and staying in the mother land for 8 years from the age of 6. he has emerged to show his potential for the entertainment industry With Many talents and skills he possesses, namely music production, song writing, music composing,rapping, voice impersonations , comedy various sports activities such as swimming,golfing,tennis, ice skating,rollerblading,skateboarding, ice skating ,horseback riding all topped off with a passion for Motorsport and anything on wheels. Robert also performs a variety of hip hop from the hip trendy hype type of rap down to the lyrical conscious hip hop you name it. Starting music at the age of ten and creating over thirty songs one of which “Famous” won the best African music video by minors.

Alexis Albert Akpan born in Newark, New Jersey august 7th, 2004 aka lexeye and the middle child out of three. In 2007 Alexis moved to Nigeria and lived there for 9 years and learned her culture, tradition and the life style. At the age of 3 Alexis started skating and later on did more hobbies like golf, swimming, tennis, writing, singing, skating, ice skating and horse back riding . At the age of 10 Alexis did back ups for her brother songs Robert albert (aka young Bobby) and later on eleveated to singing the chorus and both became a duo. Over the year Alexis and her brother (Robert) were nominated and awarded for African Music Video Awards with their hit song “Famous”. Alexis is originated in a state in Nigeria called Akwa ibom state.

From pre-k to the third grade, Alexis attended palm court crèche and school and later on moved to her hometown akwa ibom state.

Where she finished elementary at ray-field elementary and graduated to bright future college middle school and in August 2016 Alexis was moved to Atlanta, Georgia to complete her middle school studies at hull middle school.
